T

toString() - Method in class economy.Agent
Returns a string representation of the current agent which is of the form: "A" with $B and C. where A is the current agent's name, B is the current agent's amount of money, and C is the current agent's inventory's string representation.
toString() - Method in class economy.Inventory
Returns a string representation of the current inventory of the form: QTY1x"ITEM1", QTY2x"ITEM2", QTY3x"ITEM3", ..., QTYnx"ITEMn" where QTYk is the quantity of ITEMk which is the kth item in the current inventory.
toString() - Method in class economy.Item
Returns a string representation of this item of the form: "NAME" where NAME is the name of this item.
toString() - Method in class economy.Market
Returns a string representation of the current market of the form: ITEMS: {
  ITEM1, ITEM2, ITEM3, ..., ITEMn
}
AGENTS: {
  AGENT1,
  AGENT2,
  AGENT3,
  ...,
  AGENTn
} where ITEMk denotes the string representation of the kth item in the list of items which exist in the current market and AGENTk denotes the string representation of the kth agent in the list of agents which exist in the current market.
